Patch Set 11: Code-Review-1

patch is working as expected, but it would be better to have fixed yaml format with initail value is 0, then collector could be easy to parse stats?
e.g. 
  read_bytes:      { samples: 2, ..., hist: { 32: 0, 64: 0, 128: 1, 256: 0, 512: 0, 1K: 1 } }
  write_bytes:     { samples: 1, ..., hist: { 32: 1, 64: 0, } }

but it could make too long line for all jobstats?

Patch Set 11:

After checking the codes again, I think we might be able to find a way to extend XML to support the new format.

@Feng Lei, would you please provide a full example of the /proc file output? I'd like to try to parse the file to confirm Collectd works as expected.

